While it's great that Confluence Mobile shows to users on smartphones and those with small screens, it is arguable that users on tablet devices do not require Confluence Mobile due to the screen resolutions and processing power available to them on their device.

Therefore, administrators should be able to (at least) disable showing Confluence Mobile to users who have tablets. At most, a fully populated list of devices (e.g., "Show to iPhone 5", "Hide from iPhone 3", etc.) should be made available for toggling in the administration panel

