As Jira doesn't require custom field names to be unique, its possible to have inaccessible custom fields due to their name.

An example would be a user naming their custom field "Priority", as they wish to use some custom measurement of the priority of an issue, which cannot be fully described by the default system. When they attempt to reference their own Priority field in the Issues Macro, they instead receive the default Priority, as there is no way of distinguishing between the two fields, rendering their custom field undisplayable.

Allowing referencing by ID would resolve this problem.

